<item>
            <title>[LU-654] Select machinefile option for mpirun via a variable.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-654</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Not all MPI implementations pass the host file to mpirun via the same&lt;br/&gt;
option. Common options are -machinefile and -hostfile. Modify mpi_run&lt;br/&gt;
to use MACHINEFILE_OPTION instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached patch showed we replaced &quot;-machinefile&quot; with $MACHINEFILE_OPTION. It does not need to be named that way. Just a meaning variable will be fine. Also, our patch did not give a default value should MACHINEFILE_OPTION not defined. Maybe cfg/local.sh a good place?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Signed-off-by: Jason Rappleye &amp;lt;jason.rappleye@nasa.gov&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Signed-off-by: Jay Lan &amp;lt;jay.j.lan@nasa.gov&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>1.8.6 servers running centos5.6 and 1.8.6 clients running sles11sp1.</environment>
